   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,129:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Comprehensive Project Report: Live Real Estate Price Estimator
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,130:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (Quetta)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,131:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1. Executive Summary 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,132:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,132:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Introduction
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,133:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,135:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Live Real Estate Price Estimator
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,141:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is a highly dynamic, Python-based full-stack machine learning application.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,142:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The primary objective is to reliably predict the financial cost of residential plots in Quetta, Pakistan.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,161:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A fundamental flaw in traditional machine learning deployments for real estate is their reliance on static datasets
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (e.g., CSV files exported months or years ago). Real estate markets are highly volatile; prices fluctuate wildly based
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,170:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: on macroeconomic factors, inflation, and local developments. To solve this, this project pioneers a 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Just-In-Time
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,172:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,172:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,173:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (JIT) data extraction and training methodology
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . Rather than querying an outdated database, the application
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: actively scrapes the current, live HTML listings directly from the premier Pakistani real estate portal, 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,180:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Zameen.com
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,186:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . The AI model trains on this live data dynamically, guaranteeing that all predictions are accurately grounded in the exact market conditions of the present moment.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,187:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2. System Architecture 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,187:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  High-Level Workflow
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The application is decoupled into three primary architectural pipelines, seamlessly connected via an interactive
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: graphical frontend:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step 2.1: Trigger 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  On-Demand Execution
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,193:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Upon application startup, the system halts and awaits user input regarding data freshness. The user can request 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,193:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: N
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,194:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,195:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: pages of data from the UI. Clicking the 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,195:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,196:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fetch Live Data
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,196:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,197:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  operational button triggers the backend scraper via Python
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,198:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,198:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: st.spinner
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  contextual block, maintaining UI responsiveness while networking occurs.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,200:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step 2.2: The Live Data Extraction Pipeline
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The system utilizes 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Requests
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,202:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  to fire HTTP GET requests natively to Zameen.com
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,202:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,206:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s Quetta index. Recognizing
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: that modern web portals employ bot-mitigation, the requests perfectly spoof a standard user-agent (
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Mozilla/5.0
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Windows NT 10.0
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,209:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ). Once an HTTP 200 (OK) response is met, the raw HTML is piped immediately into 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,209:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BeautifulSoup
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,210:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  where Document Object Model (DOM) traversal isolates the 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,211:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <li>
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,212:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  structures representing
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: individual plot listings.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step 2.3: Transformation 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  ETL (Extract, Transform, Load)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The raw data is extremely messy strings: (e.g., 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,216:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Price: 1.5 Crore
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,219:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Size: 1 Kanal
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,219:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ). The application passes this
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: through Regex-powered transformation functions.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1 Kanal
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,224:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,225:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  undergoes numerical transformation through multiplication (
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,226:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1 Kanal * 20 = 20
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,226:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Marlas
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,227:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ).
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,227:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,228:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,228:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1.5 Crore
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,229:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,230:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is analytically mapped 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,230:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,231:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1.5 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,231:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: *
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,232:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  10,000,000 = 15,000,000 PKR
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,232:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: )
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,233:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,234:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,235:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The standardized output
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,236:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: is loaded elegantly into a structured 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,236:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Pandas DataFrame
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,237:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,238:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step 2.4: Just-In-Time Model Training
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,239:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This Pandas DataFrame acts as the immediate training set. The data passes through a Scikit-Learn 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,240:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ColumnTransformer
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,240:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  executing a 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,241:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OneHotEncoder
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,244:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  algorithm, mapping categorical boundaries (Location
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,245:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Strings) to binary vectors. Finally, it drops into the 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,246:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: RandomForestRegressor
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,250:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , spawning a forest of decision
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,251:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trees that individually assess the feature splits, compiling into a singular, highly accurate pricing metric.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,251:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step 2.5: User Querying 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,252:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Output
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,254:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The model and dataset are injected deep into Streamlit
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,254:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,255:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,255:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: session_state
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,268:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , ensuring subsequent inputs do not
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: re-trigger the heavy scraping pipeline. The user interacts with high-level graphical sliders, and in roughly ~15
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: milliseconds, the pipeline processes the single row DataFrame through the pipeline and outputs the estimated price
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: formatting.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-12 21:59:32,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3. Comprehensive Technology Stack Analysis
